  <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:0cm 5.75pt 0cm 5.75pt'>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The Riktoh are average height, amiable Ursidians. Th=
ey
  have no separate nose for breathing or smell, this is all done through th=
eir
  mouth and makes the Riktoh look like they are constantly panting. </p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>For the Riktoh their greatest importance is wealth, =
they
  are always looking for a way to get rich fast and go to great risks to do=
 so.
  Despite this desire they generally don't consider taking riches from anot=
her
  being an option, being a mostly law abiding race. Conversations with a Ri=
ktoh
  generally just concentrate on what belongings they have, how big their ho=
mes
  are and other displays of wealth. </p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>For many Riktoh they realised in the dawn of the spa=
ce age
  for their race it was a great opportunity to get extremely rich, many jum=
ped
  in ill equipped space craft just for the opportunity to be one of the fir=
st
  to find what is out there. </p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The Riktoh are a bit wary of other races naturally b=
ut are
  usually very willing to trade and are very dependable friends.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Cautious by nature the Riktoh have pioneered the abi=
lity
  to disrupt Hyperdrive use for a limited range in space.<span
  style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>The Space Denial 5000S was devel=
oped
  for a forseen need for early warning of planetary attacks by outside
  aggressors.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The Riktoh live in small communities, where land is =
divided
  up by wealth. Border disputes are common and within their communities Rik=
toh
  will often have fierce rivalries and few friendships.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The Riktoh preferred weapon is the Missile and they =
focus
  on Speed and Agility with Energy Research.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'><o:p>&nbsp;<=
/o:p></i></p>
